BODY.RESULTS.INFLAMMATION.
The peak increments in plasma cortisol, glucagon, IL-6, IL-10 and TNF-α all had a significant (all, P < 0.005) positive correlation with the peak increment of sCD163 (Fig. 4 and Table 1). Additionally, the peak in body temperature and heart rate also correlated significantly (both, P < 0.005) with the peak concentration of sCD163 (Table 1).
